<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My notes say this is a dropped spell.  So does anyone have any hints for me as to where it does drop? Because I have NEVER seen it drop.<P>LOL<P>Thanks!<P>------------------<BR><B>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara</B><BR>Templar of Tunare<BR><B>~Calizana Rhinelander</B><BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR>Farstorm ~ Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Panteroo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have seen this spell drop in three locations:<P>1. Skyfire Mountains - got one off a Faerie of Dismay<BR>2. Sebilis - Juggs & Reets in lower OS before Trakanon<BR>3. Sebilis - Emperor past Rare Hall<P>Best bet (IMHO) is grab a high level necro and rogue and go to Skyfire and fear-kite til you drop... the other two locations require a full group or more. Plus all the solo'ers there love having a cleric around if things go bad, i was donated a copy of Fortitude and Aegis just for doing rez's there while I was hunting with some friends.<P>my 2cp<P><P>------------------<BR>Panteroo Mcgillakudy<BR>Patriarch of the Patron Saints<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Balamor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sorry Pants, gotta interject here :P<P>I have seriously spent over 200 hours worth of exping/spell farming in skyfire and never once saw a single naltron's mark drop. Just ask Seriena hehe<P>In 5 or 6 juggs raids, we have gotten it 3 times so far<P>------------------<BR>58 Dorf Templar<BR>Soldiers of Light<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We got 1 copy on a jugg raid not that long ago.<BR>Was my first raid so I can't say anything about how rare it is.<BR>I've been to some Trak raids though and while clearing our way there, I haven't seen any drop yet.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The best way to get a particular spell you need is to buy it.  Camping Skyfire or Juggs or the various other camps for a *single* spell will more likely than not yield only frustration.  Now, if you need lots of 55+ spells, then go for it, because your odds of a needed drop are better.<P>Naltron's Mark can be purchased for 10k or less on most servers.  Given a 30 hours or so of xp grinding you'll net 10k in twink gear + gems + cash + rez $$.  Then you can go auctioning for it.  Besides, you'll get good xp during those hours.<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Got my copy on a Juggs/Reets raid.  Actually we got 2 copies this day which was sweet.  <P>Getting people to camp Juggs/Reets in my old guild was like pulling teeth.  All of the casters wanted to go, but it was EXTREMELY difficult to get a couple of tanks since nothing dropped for them.  We finally got two solid groups down there and grabbed a couple of copies.  Very nice considering that on our various times to Trakanon, we never saw anything but Magician, Enchanter, and Druid spells.<P>One of my Druid friends has picked up a copy or two in Skyfire as well.  The last time he got one, I was level 56 so the spell went to someone else.<P>As to which is more common, I can't really say.  Both places suck in their own ways and buying it isn't, necessarily, an option.  The problem is that it's rare and can be extremely hard to find.  If you have the cash though, it's not a bad route to go.  However 10k = 900 Peridots.  The mana it saves is great but, if you buy it, the money you save isn't.<P>Edit: I added an extra zero to the final paragraph.<P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Templar of 58 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<P>Islington Angelwatch <BR>Cavalier of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<p>[This message has been edited by Islington (edited 12-13-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">>>However 10k = 9000 Peridots. The mana it saves is great but, if you buy it, the money you save isn't.<P>Actually at 10.5pp per peridot (the best possible price from a merchant) its 952 peridots.<P>Last night is a good example for use in comparison.  I xp'd for 8 hours in a zone where I needed symbol, but didn't really need Martzin.  I used about 12 peridots with Naltron's Mark (1 per hour + 4 for rebuffs, new people, etc).  If I was using Martzin, it would have cost 48 peridots (6 per hour, we'll assume no rebuff).  <P>So lastnight alone I saved 378pp in peridots.  It will take a while to hit the break even point, but that spell will eventually pay for itself.<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sollwin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Got mine as a drop in Skyfire, we were just goofing off.  Got it at lvl 52, so it wook a bit before I could use it, hehe.<P>------------------<BR>Sollwin Lifestar<BR>58th Halfling Templar of Bristlebane<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41743" TARGET=_blank>Inspect Me!</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Quantas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i also got mine in SF think off a guardian Wurm or somthing.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f